RACE.RACE_TEXT: CANTERBURY PARK RACE 1 1M Turf CR: 79. Claiming Purse 12000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES OR MINNESOTA BRED WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $10,000. Minnesota Bred Claiming Price $15,000. (If management deems it inadvisable to run this race on the Turf, it will be run at a distance of 1 Mile on the main track.).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: I'M NOBLE was rank around the first turn on the inside off the pace, then moved through on the rail to co-lead down the backstretch, matching strides with KURT'S CHOICE to the top of the stretch then edged away, dug in when MY CALANTE challenged him in mid stretch and held on. MY CALANTE was allowed to settle near the back down the backstretch while racing four or five wide then tipped in to save ground around the final turn, made a rail bid in the stretch but was not enough but proved second best. GLENDALE raced in the middle of the pack around the first turn then moved up from three or four wide down the backstretch then went three wide into upper stretch, drifted out to mid track and kept on rally for the show. LITTLE RED RIFLE hustled along early to press the pace from the two path around the first turn then settled off the pace down the backstretch and around the final turn then made a rebid in early stretch but only passed tiring rival. KURT'S CHOICE broke well and went to the front around the first turn then was engaged entering the backstretch by I'M NOBLE and co-led to the top of the stretch, drifted out in mid stretch and tired. CALICO JOE was off a step slow and was allowed to settle at the back of the pack but never made a serious bid.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CANTERBURY PARK RACE 2 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 66. Maiden Special Weight Purse 31000. FOR MN-BRED MAIDENS, TWO YEARS OLD. Weight, 118 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: OUTOFTHEDARK broke in and bumped with GOT GHOSTED at the start, kept on to prompt the pace from the two path and took the lead at the eighth pole while racing erratic down the stretch but kept on and drew clear. GOT GHOSTED had an awkward start, broke out and bumped with OUTOFTHEDARK and CARPE GOLD leaving the gate, then hustled up to be off the pace from between horses, moved out to three wide in upper stretch and tipped in to two wide at the eighth pole to prove second best. KIRILL THE THRILL was forwardly placed from three wide around the turn then tucked to the inside at the three sixteenths pole but had to maneuver through traffic at the eighth pole but was a game third. JONNY B GONEY was slow into his stride leaving the gate then rushed up from four wide to vie for the lead around the turn but floated out going into the stretch and weakened. BENZ LAKE THUNDER broke well then settled in the middle of the pack and passed tiring rivals in the stretch. CARPE GOLD was bumped by GOT GHOSTED at the start, raced near the back and was not a threat. EXPOUND had good speed through the turn then was headed by OUTOFTHEDARK at the three sixteenths pole, drifted in at the eighth pole and tired. JOSH'S DRAMA was off the early pace then dropped back on the turn and was outrun. A JOCKEY OBJECTION WAS POSTED, THE JOCKEY OF GOT GHOSTED CLAIMED FOUL AGAINST THE JOCKEY OF OUTOFTHEDARK FOR ALLEGED INTERFERENCE LEAVING THE STARTING GATE, AFTER A STEWARDS REVIEW THE CLAIM OF FOUL WAS DISALLOWED AND NO ACTION WAS TAKEN.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CANTERBURY PARK RACE 3 7 1/2F Turf CR: 71. Maiden Special Weight Purse 31000. FOR MN-BRED MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE, FOUR, AND FIVE YEARS OLD. (If management deems it inadvisable to run this race on the turf, two-year-old races will be run at 6 and 1/2 furlongs and races for three-y ear-olds and up will be run at a distance of 1 mile on the main track.).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MIDNIGHT LANE tracked the leaders down the backstretch from three wide then moved up around the final turn, engaged the leader at the three sixteenths pole and was bumped by KOOKYBERRY near the eighth pole but kept on to prevail. KOOKYBERRY sprinted to the front to set the pace for the first quarter, edged away on the final turn to a clear lead but ducked in around the three sixteenths pole then angled out and bumped with MIDNIGHT LANE near the eighth pole and fought gamely to the wire to be second best. STRABELLA hopped out of the gate and trailed the field around the first turn then hustled along down the backstretch and moved between horses going into the final turn, moved out to three wide in upper stretch and made a late run to be best of the rest. HONEYCRISP saved ground to no avail. DANZONBY stalked the pace from the two path around the first turn, moved up from four wide down the backstretch then dropped back on the final turn and was not a factor. GRACE A'LACE pressed the pace from the two path around the first turn then took a brief lead on the backstretch and continued to press the pace to midway through the final turn and tired. A JOCKEY OBJECTION WAS POSTED, THE JOCKEY OF KOOKYBERRY CLAIMED FOUL AGAINST THE JOCKEY OF MIDNIGHT LANE FOR ALLEGED INTERFERENCE AT THE TOP OF THE STRETCH, AFTER A STEWARDS REVIEW THE CLAIM OF FOUL WAS DISALLOWED AND NO ACTION WAS TAKEN.
